{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Parents from Russia and the Middle East are often unfamiliar with the signs of drug abuse and may not know how to navigate the world of treatment and recovery....", "abstract": "Opioid abuse, including heroin and prescription pills, is spreading to immigrants in South Brooklyn neighborhoods, catching many families unfamiliar with signs of drug abuse off guard; treatment centers and organizations are working to fight cultural stigmas associated with drug abuse within these communities' in order to administer treatment to those in need.", "section_name": "N.Y. / Region", "print_page": "21", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Liz", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ROBBINS", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By LIZ ROBBINS"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/22/nyregion/heroin-and-pill-overdoses-claim-immigrant-victims-catching-families-off-guard.html", "lead_paragraph": "Parents from Russia and the Middle East are often unfamiliar with the signs of drug abuse and may not know how to navigate the world of treatment and recovery.", "headline": {"main": "Heroin and Pill Overdoses Claim Immigrant Victims, Catching Families Off Guard", "print_headline": "Overdoses Claim Immigrant Victims, Catching Families Off Guard"}, "_id": "5790ffaa38f0d87a83eba6a3", "word_count": "1572", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/07/21/nyregion/22HEROIN1/22HEROIN1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/07/21/nyregion/22HEROIN1/22HEROIN1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2016/07/21/nyregion/22HEROIN1/22HEROIN1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/07/21/nyregion/22HEROIN1/22HEROIN1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2016/07/21/nyregion/22HEROIN1/22HER